summary:
Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse - SDCC 2018 “photo” 

Phil Lord and Christopher Miller, the creative minds behind The Lego...
caption:
Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse - SDCC 2018 “photo”

Phil Lord and Christopher Miller, the creative minds behind The Lego Movie and 21 Jump Street, bring their unique talents to a fresh vision of a different Spider-Man Universe, with a groundbreaking visual style that’s the first of its kind. Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse introduces Brooklyn teen Miles Morales, and the limitless possibilities of the Spider-Verse, where more than one can wear the mask.

December 14, 2018.

We would normally pass on just a still like this but Nelson wanted to post it because of Spider-Gwen.

Peter: He’s my…

Peter: Uncle!

body:
Y’all. I just realized something.

Liz is a brave gal for automatically assuming Peter liked her when he first confessed it. Like, girl was like “bitch, I already know. It’s kind of obvious.”

LIKE. BITCH. YOU WERE BRAVE TO ASSUME HE LIKED YOU.

WHAT IF HE DIDNT? WHAT IF HE WAS JUST SWEET, SHY, AND NICE TO EVERYONE?

Like… damn. She was quick to assume. SHE BRAVE.

If someone confessed to me that they had a crush on me, I’d be like… “lol u sure? You could do so much better, mah dude” 😂

title:
Siobhan Reviews Movies: 
Spider-Man Homecoming
body:
I’m going to keep this one short because I presently feel like I’m going to die

Great movie. Perfect Spider-Man movie, really. Great villain ( both relateable and badass. I mean, if you had the means, wouldn’t you use alien tech to make money to look after your family? ) epic twist. Great characters. I’m glad Marvel got to do Spider-Man finally, because they did good

Downside: yet more high school drama I couldn’t relate to.

10/10 and a giant bird man with a relateable back story
